{"word":"λυσσάω","slug":"λυσσάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λυσσάω</b></el> <el>(λυσσάω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λύσσα'><el>λύσσα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be raging</i> in battle, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to rave, be mad</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of dogs, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; of wolves, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}